    "createpropulsion.ponder.hot_air_pump.header": "Using Hot Air Pump",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.hot_air_pump.text_1": "Hot air pumps can be used to create balloons and fill them with hot air.",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.hot_air_pump.text_2": "Hot air pump must be placed on active heat source...",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.hot_air_pump.text_3": "... and rotation must be provided for it to function.",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.hot_air_pump.text_4": "Amount of hot air produced depends on RPM.",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.hot_air_pump.text_5": "At 256 RPM Hot Air Pump outputs the most amount of hot air.",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.liquid_burner.header": "Generating heat with Liquid Burner",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.liquid_burner.text_1": "Liquid Burners burn liquid fuels to provide heat to consumers directly above them",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.liquid_burner.text_10": "Liquid Burners can be chained together.",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.liquid_burner.text_11": "They will act as a pipe and pass fuel to other Liquid Burners.",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.liquid_burner.text_2": "Heat consumers will activate the burner once fueled",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.liquid_burner.text_3": "Heat output is automatically regulated for fuel efficiency",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.liquid_burner.text_4": "Liquid Burners produce twice as much heat, compared to Solid Burners",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.liquid_burner.text_5": "Liquid Burners feature an internal thermostat",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.liquid_burner.text_6": "Applying a Redstone signal will disable the thermostat",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.liquid_burner.text_7": "While disabled, fuel is consumed at a constant rate, even without a consumer on top",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.liquid_burner.text_8": "§fBurner Status: §6Hot",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.liquid_burner.text_9": "§fBurner Status: §cSearing",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.making_balloon.header": "Making a Hot Air Balloon",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.making_balloon.text_1": "Envelopes encase volume that can be filled with hot air.",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.making_balloon.text_2": "Hot Air Burners will fill balloons above them, when fueled.",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.making_balloon.text_3": "Hot Air Burners must not be further than 5 blocks from the open bottom of the balloon.",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.making_balloon.text_4": "Hot air output can be controlled by clicking on the lever.",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.making_balloon.text_5": "Hot Air Burner has 3 power levels.",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.making_balloon.text_6": "The higher is power level - the higher is hot air output.",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.redstone_transmission_direct.header": "Transmission Control Mode: Direct",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.redstone_transmission_direct.text_1": "Transmission has 2 control modes, and direct mode is default.",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.redstone_transmission_direct.text_2": "In direct control mode, transmission outputs RPM proportional to the redstone input on either side.",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.redstone_transmission_direct.text_3": "Note that the output speed is scaled from 0 to the input speed.",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.redstone_transmission_incremental.header": "Transmission Control Mode: Incremental",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.redstone_transmission_incremental.text_1": "Transmission in incremental control mode outputs speed proportional to the internal shift level.",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.redstone_transmission_incremental.text_2": "You can change the control mode with a scroll selection box at the back of the transmission.",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.redstone_transmission_incremental.text_3": "Redstone signal given to the side with + (plus) sign will increase the shift level.",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.redstone_transmission_incremental.text_4": "Redstone signal given to the side with - (minus) sign will decrease the shift level.",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.redstone_transmission_incremental.text_5": "If the signal is given to both sides...",
    "createpropulsion.ponder.redstone_transmission_incremental.text_6": "...the transmission will perform both addition and subtraction.",
